  "intro": "The verb poder means to be able to or can. In the present tense, use it to talk about ability, permission, and things that are possible.",
  "overview": {
    "body": "Poder is an irregular verb in the present tense. The stem changes from o to ue in puedo, puedes, puede, and pueden, but nosotros keeps the regular stem: podemos.",
